  "text": "dsRNA, not siRNA, induces QDE-2 expression, and DCLs are required for the maintenance of QDE-2 levels posttranscriptionally. The low levels of QDE-2 in the dcl-1 ko dcl-2 rip double mutant (Fig. 1A) suggest that DCLs are required for the maintenance of steady-state levels of QDE-2. Further supporting this notion, we found that the induction of dsRNA in the dcl-1 ko dcl-2 rip double mutant failed to increase the level of QDE-2 ( Fig. 2A) . In contrast, QDE-1 was not required for the induction of QDE-2 by dsRNA. It has been previously shown that QDE-1 is not required for gene silencing when dsRNA is produced from an exogenous hairpin construct [CITATION_1] .",
